Ticket ID: AI-DEV-2026-02-24-04
Title: Structured AI Usage Framework for Personal Projects and Skill Development
Classification: AI Utilization Strategy / Professional Development
Execution Date: 24 February 2026
Status: Active
Executive Summary
This ticket documents the implementation of a structured methodology for using AI agents to support personal projects, documentation cleanup, learning activities, and professional development.
The objective is to improve the user’s ability to interact efficiently with different AI systems and to develop practical expertise in prompt engineering and AI-assisted workflows.
Current AI Usage Scope
AI tools are currently used for:
	• organizing personal project documentation
	• improving written material
	• learning and experimentation
	• supporting complex research tasks
	• assisting with portfolio development
The user intentionally works with multiple AI agents in order to compare capabilities and understand their respective strengths and limitations.
Operational Methodology
AI interactions follow a structured workflow:
	1. Define a clear objective.
	2. Break the task into modular requests.
	3. Validate outputs carefully.
	4. Iterate and refine prompts.
	5. Document the results as portfolio case studies.
This approach transforms AI interactions into structured learning and productivity exercises.
Long-Term Objective
The long-term objective of this system is to develop strong practical competence in:
	• prompt engineering
	• AI workflow design
	• AI-assisted research
	• structured documentation generation
All AI-assisted projects are documented through dedicated tickets in order to track experimentation results and improve the methodology over time.

Ticket ID: AI-RES-2026-02-24-05
Title: Exploration and Evaluation of Alternative AI Agents for Complex Analytical Tasks
Classification: AI Tools Evaluation / Workflow Optimization
Execution Date: 24 February 2026
Status: Planned
Executive Summary
This ticket documents the ongoing effort to evaluate alternative AI systems that may provide improved reliability when handling complex analytical or structured data tasks.
The evaluation process is motivated by previously observed limitations when using certain AI agents for large multi-module projects such as financial modeling and tax calculation tools.
Evaluation Objectives
The goal of the evaluation is to identify AI systems that demonstrate stronger performance in areas such as:
	• structured data reasoning
	• spreadsheet architecture design
	• financial modeling
	• complex logical frameworks
Evaluation Strategy
The evaluation will involve:
	• testing different AI agents with identical prompts
	• comparing output quality
	• measuring hallucination frequency
	• analyzing consistency of results
	• validating technical accuracy
Optimization Focus
The prompt strategy will also be refined in order to improve compatibility with different AI systems.
This includes:
	• simplifying prompt instructions
	• separating complex requests into smaller tasks
	• validating outputs incrementally
Expected Outcome
The evaluation process will allow the user to determine which AI agents are best suited for specific categories of tasks, thereby improving overall productivity and reliability of AI-assisted workflows.

